SUMMARY:Bangladesh: Humiliation\, Carnage\, Liberation\, Chaos
DESCRIPTION:December 1971\, Bangladesh. \nFor the first time\, a liberated state. No longer East Pakistan. A hard-won independence\, a people pulled through civil war\, a refugee crisis\, the guerrilla campaigns of the Mukti Bahini\, and the military engagement of the Indian Armed Forces. \nThrough recordings of officers who fought in the war\, archival footage\, and maps\, Subroto Chattopadhyay and Anil P Dere bring the reach and complexity of this history to life. The presentation draws on years of research by The Peninsula Studios into one of the most consequential geopolitical events of the twentieth century. \nThe session will open to the audience for questions. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/bangladesh-humiliation-carnage-liberation-chaos/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:History,Politics,Society
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/Thumbnail-1Bang.jpg
END:VEVENT
